Juan Manuel Alvarez, convicted of causing a deadly Los Angeles train crash, faces life in prison without parole after a jury's recommendation.
Prosecutors argued Alvarez intentionally caused the Metrolink commuter line accident in 2005 for attention.
Despite defense claims of a suicide attempt gone wrong, the judge upheld murder charges.
Alvarez, seeking forgiveness, testified he never meant harm to others.
The trial delved into Alvarez's troubled past, including abuse and drug addiction.
Family members shared emotional testimonies, painting a picture of a violent upbringing.
The fate of Alvarez now rests with the jury, deciding between life imprisonment or the death penalty.
